article.headline: Delaware St. 28, Norfolk St. 21, OT
article.story: DOVER, Del. (AP) -- Delaware State rallied from 18 points down in the fourth quarter, and linebacker Eric Sewell caught a 2-yard touchdown in overtime to give the Hornets a 28-21 victory over Norfolk State and the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference title. The game ended when Akeem Green sacked Norfolk State's Casey Hansen on fourth down in overtime, touching off a celebration for the Hornets, who won their seventh straight and secured their first outright MEAC championship since 1989. Trailing 21-3, Delaware State (9-1, 7-0) began its comeback when Shaheer McBride hit Vashon Winton for a 6-yard touchdown with 8:09 remaining. After a Norfolk State punt, Winton completed a 53-yard pass to Derrick McNeil to set up a first-and-goal at the 2. Adam Shrewsbury plowed ahead for the score, then rushed for a two-point conversion to make it 21-18. Norfolk State had a chance to run out the clock but failed to pick up a first down, giving the Hornets the ball back with 1:54 left. Delaware State drove 46 yards to set up the tying score, Peter Gaertner's 28-yard field goal as time expired. Winton went 28-of-44 for 245 yards and two touchdowns and completed passes to 11 different receivers. He also rushed for 61 yards on 18 carries. Norfolk State (7-3, 6-2) led 14-0 at the end of the first quarter on Hansen's 5-yard pass to Jamar Johnson and Daryl Jones' 16-yard run. Jones finished with 108 yards and two touchdowns on 24 carries. Gaertner got Delaware State on the board with a 39-yard field goal midway through the third quarter, but on the ensuing possession, Norfolk State took a 21-3 lead on Jones' 19-yard run.
